Package com.twitter.common.args.constraints

Interface Summary
Verifier<T> Typedef for a constraint verifier.
 

Class Summary
CanReadFileVerifier Verifier to ensure that a file is readable.
CanWriteFileVerifier Verifier to ensure that a file can be written to.
ExistsFileVerifier Verifier to ensure that a file exists.
IsDirectoryFileVerifier Verifier to ensure that a file is a directory.
NotEmptyIterableVerifier Verifies that an iterable is not empty.
NotEmptyStringVerifier Verifier to ensure that a string is not empty.
NotNegativeNumberVerifier Verifier to ensure that a number is non-negative.
NotNullVerifier A verifier that ensures a value is non-null.
PositiveNumberVerifier Verifier to ensure that a number is positive.
RangeNumberVerifier Verifies that a number (inclusively) lies within a range.
ScalarVerifier<T> Partial verifier implementation to simplify implementation of scalar verifiers.
 

Annotation Types Summary
CanRead Annotation that indicates an entity must be readable.
CanWrite Annotation that indicates an entity must be writable.
Exists Annotation that indicates an entity must exist.
IsDirectory Annotation that indicates an entity must represent a directory.
NotEmpty Annotation that indicates that an entity is non-empty.
NotNegative Annotation that indicates that an entity is non-negative.
NotNull Annotation to indicate that an entity must be non-null.
Positive Annotation that indicates an entity must be positive.
Range Annotation that indicates a field must be within a given numeric range.
